  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Conventions\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Counter-Terrorism and Proceeds of Crime Act\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction reporting\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Securities regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n\n6. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Enhanced monitoring of financial transactions\n- Mandatory risk assessments\n- Compliance training programs\n- Internal control systems\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigative efforts\n\nThis framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
